{"text_koine":"Θησεὺς ἐν οἴκῳ ἐστίν. λέγει· πεινῶ καὶ διψῶ· πορεύομαι νῦν πρὸς τὴν ἀγοράν.","text_english":"Theseus is in the house. He says: I am hungry and I am thirsty; I go now to the market.","art_instructions":"Inside a cozy home, Theseus the Owl speaks with a small speech bubble; thought icons show bread and water. Morning light at the door.","art_characters":"Theseus the Owl"}
{"text_koine":"ἔρχεται ἔξω πρὸς τὴν ὁδόν. ἐνταῦθα τέσσαρες ὁδοί εἰσιν.","text_english":"He comes out to the road. Here there are four roads.","art_instructions":"A four-way crossroads: mountain, forest, cave, and a sunlit road to a tiny agora in the distance. Soft silhouettes of the Sphinx, Cyclops, and Cerberus mark three paths.","art_characters":"Theseus the Owl; Sphinx; Cyclops; Cerberus"}
{"text_koine":"Θησεὺς εἰς τὸ ὄρος πορεύεται.","text_english":"Theseus goes into the mountain.","art_instructions":"Theseus steps onto a rocky mountain path with gentle slopes and stones.","art_characters":"Theseus the Owl"}
{"text_koine":"τέρατα ἐν τῷ ὄρει· ἡ Σφίγξ ἐστίν. δεινή ἐστιν.","text_english":"Monsters are in the mountain: the Sphinx is there. She is fierce.","art_instructions":"Friendly, non-scary Sphinx blocks the narrow mountain path, calm pose, clear that the way is closed.","art_characters":"Theseus the Owl; Sphinx"}
{"text_koine":"Θησεὺς λέγει· οὐδαμῶς. ἐκ τοῦ ὄρους ἐξέρχεται. πορεύεται ἄλλην ὁδόν.","text_english":"Theseus says: no way. He goes out of the mountain. He goes another road.","art_instructions":"Theseus turns back from the Sphinx and heads down toward the crossroads.","art_characters":"Theseus the Owl"}
{"text_koine":"Θησεὺς εἰς τὸ δάσος πορεύεται.","text_english":"Theseus goes into the forest.","art_instructions":"Theseus enters a leafy green forest path with dappled light.","art_characters":"Theseus the Owl"}
{"text_koine":"τέρατα ἐν τῷ δάσει· ὁ Κύκλωψ ἐστίν. δεινός ἐστιν.","text_english":"Monsters are in the forest: the Cyclops is there. He is fierce.","art_instructions":"A big, simple Cyclops shape among trees blocks the path; friendly colors, non-scary expression.","art_characters":"Theseus the Owl; Cyclops"}
{"text_koine":"Θησεὺς λέγει· οὐδαμῶς. ἐκ τοῦ δάσους ἐξέρχεται. πορεύεται ἄλλην ὁδόν.","text_english":"Theseus says: no way. He goes out of the forest. He goes another road.","art_instructions":"Theseus calmly leaves the forest path back toward the crossroads.","art_characters":"Theseus the Owl"}
{"text_koine":"Θησεὺς εἰς τὸ σπήλαιον πορεύεται.","text_english":"Theseus goes into the cave.","art_instructions":"Theseus approaches and steps into a soft-lit cave entrance path.","art_characters":"Theseus the Owl"}
{"text_koine":"τέρατα ἐν τῷ σπηλαίῳ· ὁ Κέρβερος ἐστίν. δεινός ἐστιν.","text_english":"Monsters are in the cave: Cerberus is there. He is fierce.","art_instructions":"Three-headed dog, gentle shapes, blocks the cave path; not frightening, just firmly in the way.","art_characters":"Theseus the Owl; Cerberus"}
{"text_koine":"Θησεὺς λέγει· οὐδαμῶς. ἐκ τοῦ σπηλαίου ἐξέρχεται. πορεύεται ἄλλην ὁδόν.","text_english":"Theseus says: no way. He goes out of the cave. He goes another road.","art_instructions":"Theseus turns around from Cerberus and returns toward the crossroads.","art_characters":"Theseus the Owl"}
{"text_koine":"Θησεὺς βλέπει ἀγαθὴν ὁδόν καὶ ἥλιον. τέρατα οὐκ ἔστιν ἐκεῖ.","text_english":"Theseus sees a good road and sun. There are no monsters there.","art_instructions":"Sunlit open road leading toward a small agora; the other three paths are behind and darker.","art_characters":"Theseus the Owl"}
{"text_koine":"Θησεὺς περιπατεῖ ἠρέμα· εἶτα τρέχει ταχέως· καὶ πέτεται.","text_english":"Theseus walks gently; then he runs quickly; and he flies.","art_instructions":"Sequence of Theseus first walking, then running, then lifting into a short glide toward the market.","art_characters":"Theseus the Owl"}
{"text_koine":"ἔρχεται εἰς τὴν ἀγοράν. τράπεζα ἐνταῦθα· ἄρτος καὶ ὕδωρ.","text_english":"He comes into the market. A table is here: bread and water.","art_instructions":"Friendly market stall with simple loaves and a water jug on a table; warm, welcoming scene.","art_characters":"Theseus the Owl"}
{"text_koine":"Θησεὺς λαμβάνει ἄρτον. ἐσθίει ἄρτον καὶ πίνει ὕδωρ.","text_english":"Theseus takes bread. He eats bread and drinks water.","art_instructions":"Theseus happily nibbling bread and sipping water beside the stall.","art_characters":"Theseus the Owl"}
{"text_koine":"Θησεὺς λέγει· εὐχαριστῶ.","text_english":"Theseus says: thank you.","art_instructions":"Theseus smiles and gives a small thankful gesture in the agora; sun still shining on the clear road back.","art_characters":"Theseus the Owl"}